# TypeScript/Node Build & Conventions

## TypeScript Standards

### Code Quality
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Implement proper type definitions
- Avoid `any` type except when necessary
- Use ESLint and Prettier for code formatting
- Follow Airbnb or Google style guide

### Project Structure
```
project/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts
│   ├── types/
│   ├── utils/
│   ├── services/
│   └── controllers/
├── tests/
│   ├── unit/
│   ├── integration/
│   └── e2e/
├── dist/ (build output)
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── .eslintrc.js
└── README.md
```

### Dependencies & Package Management
- Use npm or yarn for package management
- Use `package.json` for dependency management
- Implement proper versioning (semantic versioning)
- Use package-lock.json or yarn.lock for reproducible builds
- Separate dev and production dependencies

### Build Configuration
- Use TypeScript compiler (tsc) for compilation
- Configure tsconfig.json with appropriate settings
- Implement build scripts in package.json
- Use webpack or rollup for bundling if needed
- Implement source maps for debugging

### Testing Framework
- Use Jest or Mocha for unit testing
- Implement test coverage reporting
- Use Supertest for API testing
- Implement end-to-end testing with Playwright or Cypress
- Follow TDD/BDD practices

### API Design
- Use RESTful conventions
- Implement proper HTTP status codes
- Use JSON for data exchange
- Implement request/response validation
- Add comprehensive API documentation

### Security & Performance
- Implement input validation and sanitization
- Use Helmet for security headers
- Implement rate limiting
- Use compression middleware
- Optimize bundle size and loading times

### Error Handling
- Implement global error handling
- Use custom error classes
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Implement proper logging
- Handle async errors appropriately

### Database Integration
- Use ORMs like TypeORM or Prisma
- Implement connection pooling
- Use migrations for schema changes
- Implement proper transaction handling
- Add database indexes for performance